cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper presents a set of CNN-based end-to-end models for controlling a Formula SAE racecar, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with control systems and machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a network design for predicting brake and throttle, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
